00:04:35,940 --> 00:04:41,720
The principle of optimality is, well, it's an incredibly elegant piece of logic.

72
00:04:41,720 --> 00:04:53,780
Bellman stated that an optimal path, meaning the absolute most efficient way to get from a starting state to a goal state, is made entirely out of optimal subpaths.

